# Interactive Cursor

All clickable elements must use `cursor-pointer`. Disabled controls use `disabled:cursor-not-allowed`.

## Rules

- Prefer `Button` from `$lib/components/ui/button` — it includes `cursor-pointer` by default
- Raw `<button>`, `<a>`, and clickable rows (`role="option"`, menu items) must add `cursor-pointer` explicitly
- Reuse `interactive` from `$lib/components/ui/variants` for raw buttons/links:

```svelte
<button type="button" class={cn(interactive, 'text-secondary-400')}>...</button>
```

```typescript
// variants.ts
export const interactive = 'cursor-pointer disabled:cursor-not-allowed';
```

## Do not

- Leave raw clickable elements without a pointer cursor
- Use `cursor-default` on interactive elements unless they are genuinely non-clickable
